#- In the beginning, there§0
§0was nothing in the§0
§0universe except a§0
§0formless chaos, this§0
§0void was known as§0
§0Kawlijak. The chaos§0
§0coalesced into a§0
§0cosmic egg for 50,000§0
§0years. Within it, the§0
§0perfectly opposed§0
§0forces of fire and§0
§0water became§0
§0balanced. The balance§0

#- of the two forces§0
§0broke the cosmic egg§0
§0in half. Separating the§0
§0forces, and forming§0
§0their own spheres of§0
§0power, creating a§0
§0gaping hole in the§0
§0cosmic void. All water§0
§0went upwards above§0
§0the gaping hole, and§0
§0created the Gelit. All§0
§0fire went downwards§0
§0under§0

#- the gaping hole, and§0
§0created the Yucas.§0
§0The two forces§0
§0created cosmic lands§0
§0in the chaotic§0
§0universe, Gelit was§0
§0filled with ice glaciers,§0
§0rivers, and gigantic§0
§0oceans. The southern§0
§0regions of Yucas§0
§0surfaced volcanoes,§0
§0lava, and erosion filled§0
§0molten land.§0

#- The two opposite holds§0
§0lived in harmony, but§0
§0overtime they began to§0
§0expand. After 50,000§0
§0years, Gelit and Yucas§0
§0met in the middle of the§0
§0gaping void. The§0
§0meeting point of the§0
§0two forces became§0
§0known as the Uzil. The§0
§0fire from Yucas began§0
§0to melt the§0

#- icecaps on Gelit and§0
§0thus, beginning to drip,§0
§0and began to shape§0
§0the ice into a humanoid§0
§0creature. It was a§0
§0Shangel, also called a§0
§0giant, this giant was§0
§0named Azmir. Azmir was§0
§0a gigantic man, short§0
§0brown hair with dark§0
§0eyes and white hair all§0
§0over his§0

#- skin. He didn't come§0
§0alone, he was§0
§0accompanied by a§0
§0she-wolf with the name§0
§0of Azlena. She§0
§0breastfed Azmir,§0
§0nourishing him when he§0
§0was young and weak.§0
§0When Azmir rested, he§0
§0started to sweat from§0
§0the heat coming from§0
§0the Yucas. Azmir's§0
§0sweat grew into a§0

#- race of giants, over§0
§02,000 giants were§0
§0created by the sweat§0
§0of Azmir.§0
§0
§0Azlena, the wolf,§0
§0hydrated herself by§0
§0drinking from the River§0
§0Khemmoro in Uzil.§0
§0Azlena would bathe§0
§0herself in the river,§0
§0and soon give birth to§0
§0a strong, handsome,§0

#- humanoid God with the§0
§0name of Horin. Horin§0
§0later had a son called§0
§0Vodarr, with his wife§0
§0Bina. Vodarr later§0
§0married Pevon, the§0
§0daughter of the giant§0
§0Cothas, and have 8§0
§0children, 5 sons and 3§0
§0daughters. The 5 sons§0
§0were named Asgeir,§0
§0Sybaris, Zogmis, Miroki,
#- and Sana, the 3§0
§0daughters were named§0
§0Miranda, Alli, and Adri.§0
§0All together they are§0
§0named the Valda.§0
§0
§0Asgeir, and his siblings§0
§0were annoyed of the§0
§0resentment the other§0
§0creatures of Kawlijak§0
§0treated them. They§0
§0were the only§0

#- moralized Gods, while§0
§0the rest of the beings§0
§0were giants. The giants§0
§0of the lands thought§0
§0of the Valda as§0
§0inferior to them,§0
§0shoving them to the§0
§0lowest depths of Uzil.§0
§0Azmir soon banished§0
§0the Valda away from§0
§0Uzil, to the deep§0
§0caves in Yucas. The§0
§0Gods§0

#- believed the only§0
§0solution was to kill§0
§0Azmir, the father of§0
§0the giants. The Gods§0
§0waited until Azmir was§0
§0asleep before they§0
§0assassinated the giant§0
§0father, a terrifying§0
§0battle began, and by§0
§0using all their§0
§0strength they managed§0
§0to kill Azmir. The blood§0
§0of§0

#- Azmir sprouted§0
§0everywhere with a§0
§0furious force in every§0
§0direction, flooding the§0
§0entirety of Kawlijak.§0
§0Most of the giants§0
§0drowned in the huge§0
§0flood of blood, only§0
§0two giants survived§0
§0Gandite, and his wife§0
§0Cienta, the couple built§0
§0a raft to sail on until§0

#- the blood washed. All§0
§0future giants§0
§0descended from this§0
§0couple.§0
§0
§0Because of the§0
§0flooding, the Yucas,§0
§0Uzil, and Gelit were§0
§0destroyed. The Gods§0
§0dragged Azmir's§0
§0lifeless body towards§0
§0the center of Kawlijak,§0
§0and created the world§0

#- from his remains.§0
§0
§0The blood became the§0
§0oceans, rivers, and§0
§0lakes.§0
§0
§0The flesh became the§0
§0land.§0
§0
§0The bones became the§0
§0mountains.§0
§0
§0The teeth were made§0

#- into rocks.§0
§0
§0The hair became the§0
§0grass and trees.§0
§0
§0His eyes were made into the Sun and Moon.§0
§0
§0They threw the brain§0
§0up in the air and it§0
§0became the clouds, the§0
§0skull of Azmir became§0
§0the sky. The Gods§0

#- grabbed some of the§0
§0remaining sparks from§0
§0Yucas and threw them§0
§0towards the inside of§0
§0the skull, which§0
§0gleamed at night and§0
§0became the stars.§0
§0
§0Asgeir, the leader of§0
§0the Gods, created the§0
§0heavens with his own§0
§0tears and the§0
§0underworld with his§0

#- blood. He named§0
§0the heavens Asteria,§0
§0and the underworld§0
§0Ovox.§0
§0
§0But now, with his newly§0
§0built world, he had no§0
§0one to live and§0
§0protect it. Asgeir grew§0
§0fondly of his creation,§0
§0and named it Vevia§0
§0(Earth). He issued a§0
§0task to his siblings to§0

#- create the first human§0
§0beings to occupy his§0
§0beloved world. Miranda§0
§0and Sybaris both took§0
§0it upon themselves to§0
§0complete the mission.§0
§0Sybaris created§0
§0humans out of mud,§0
§0while Miranda gave§0
§0them the kiss of life.§0
§0The first two humans§0
§0were born, Melkel and§0

#- Lane. Asgeir gave them§0
§0the role to watch over§0
§0his beautiful creation,§0
§0Vevia. He allowed them§0
§0to live freely, with the§0
§0promise to protect the§0
§0world. All future§0
§0humans came from§0
§0Melkel and Lane.§0
§0
§0Asgeir instructed§0
§0every God to create a§0
§0responsibility for§0

#- themselves to help the§0
§0humans in their§0
§0struggles on Vevia.§0
§0Sybaris took it upon§0
§0himself to become§0
§0patron of the humans.§0
§0His plan was to use§0
§0the human beings§0
§0labor for his own§0
§0good, creating Vevia to§0
§0his own image. Miranda,§0
§0planning on becoming§0
§0the patron
#- Goddess of§0
§0the humans was§0
§0angered with§0
§0Sybaris that he wanted§0
§0to abuse her beautiful§0
§0creations. She§0
§0instituted war against§0
§0Sybaris, and created a§0
§0conflict between the§0
§0two siblings. They§0
§0fought for 9 days, and§0
§09 nights almost killing§0
§0each other before the§0

#- grand Asgeir split§0
§0them apart. Asgeir§0
§0gave each deity a deal§0
§0to share the humans.§0
§0Asgeir gave each§0
§0human a soul, an§0
§0embodiment spirit of§0
§0the gods. He granted§0
§0Miranda the controller§0
§0of the Asteria,§0
§0granting her control§0
§0of all worthy human's§0
§0souls, allowing
#- them to§0
§0live in Asteria with the gods.§0
§0
§0Asgeir then gave§0
§0Sybaris control of§0
§0Oxos, the underworld.§0
§0Sybaris would receive§0
§0all the evil souls of§0
§0the humans, Sybaris§0
§0would possess the§0
§0ability to punish the§0
§0humans as he pleases§0

#- and perform all the§0
§0labor he wants in his§0
§0own domain.§0
§0Soon after, the Gods§0
§0decided on their§0
§0responsibility deity§0
§0roles.§0
§0
§0Asgeir, God of the§0
§0Gods, Sky, Law, Order,§0
§0and Justice§0
§0
§0Sybaris, God of the§0

#- Underworld, Violence,§0
